  "prompt": "Upto which rank does a reserved category student get IRS (IT)?",
  "response": "The rank required for a reserved category student to get into the IRS (IT) varies each year depending on several factors, including:\n\n*   **Number of Vacancies:** The number of IRS (IT) positions available in a particular year for each reserved category significantly impacts the cutoff rank.\n*   **Exam Difficulty:** A tougher exam might lower overall scores and potentially lower the cutoff rank.\n*   **Category-wise Performance:** The performance of candidates within each reserved category affects the cutoff. If candidates in a specific category perform exceptionally well, the cutoff rank might increase.\n*   **Candidate Preferences:** The choices made by candidates during the preference filling stage also influence the allocation.\n\n**General Trends (Based on Previous Years):**\n\nWhile it's impossible to give an exact rank, here are some general trends from previous years. Please note these are indicative and can change significantly:\n\n*   **SC Category:** Ranks between 600-800 have had a decent chance to get IRS\n*   **ST Category:** Ranks between 850-1100 have had a decent chance to get IRS\n*   **OBC Category:** Ranks between 350-550 have had a decent chance to get IRS\n*   **EWS Category:** Ranks between 400-600 have had a decent chance to get IRS\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **These are estimates based on past trends and are not definitive.** Do not rely solely on these numbers.\n*   **Official cutoff ranks are released by the UPSC** after the allocation process is complete. Refer to those for the most accurate information from previous years.\n*   **Consult experienced mentors, coaching centers, or online forums** that specialize in the civil services exam. They might have more up-to-date insights.",
